def sort_by_total(df):
    df['total'] = df.sum(axis=1)
    df.sort_values(by='total',ascending=False,inplace=True)
    df.drop('total', axis=1, inplace=True)
    return df

Viz 1 - Investment, Trade, Debt, Aid¶

Charts showing:

  • Investment (FDI)
  • Trade flows
  • Debt
  • Aid

from various sectors.

  • Show the relative importance of Chinese sources of these flows
  • Show that sector-wise - the money has focused on extractive sectors

cols_pre_2012 = ['1988-89 to 2010-2011']
cols_2012_to_2015 = ['2011-12','2012-2013','2013-2014','2014-2015']
cols_2015_to_2018 = ['2015-2016','2016-2017','2017-2018','2018 (4-9)','2018-2019 (As of 31/12/2018)']
year_group_col_names = ['pre_2012','2012_to_2015','2015_to_2018']

investment_country_year_grouped_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=year_group_col_names)

investment_country_year_grouped_df['pre_2012'] = investment_country_year_df[cols_pre_2012].sum(axis=1)
investment_country_year_grouped_df['2012_to_2015'] = investment_country_year_df[cols_2013_to_2015].sum(axis=1)
investment_country_year_grouped_df['2015_to_2018'] = investment_country_year_df[cols_2015_to_2018].sum(axis=1)

    [year_group_col_names].plot(kind='bar',\

export_country_df = pd.read_csv(\
                    "../../data/trade/mmsis_export_country/mmsis_export_by_country.csv")
export_country_df.rename({"By Classification(1)": "Region", \
                          "By Classification(2)": "Country"},axis='columns',inplace=True)
export_country_df['Country'] = export_country_df['Country'].fillna('Total')
export_country_df.set_index(['Region','Country'],inplace=True)

export_country_df.replace(['-','#'], 0, inplace=True)
for c in export_country_df.columns:
    export_country_df[c] = export_country_df[c].str.replace('r', '')
    export_country_df[c] = export_country_df[c].str.replace('(', '')
    export_country_df[c] = export_country_df[c].str.replace(')', '')
    export_country_df[c] = pd.to_numeric(export_country_df[c], errors='coerce')
    export_country_df[c].fillna(0,inplace=True)
    export_country_df[c] = export_country_df[c].astype(float)
    
export_country_df.drop('Total', level=1, axis=0, inplace=True)
    
export_country_df = sort_by_total(export_country_df)
export_region_df = sort_by_total(export_region_df)

Viz 2 - Location of investments/projects¶

Show available locations for foreign investment led projects in:

  • Dams
  • Mines
  • Oil and Gas
  • Power

Data Sources¶

Dams¶

IFC Report on Hydropower in Myanmar

  • Original source - report and dataset
  • Republished with geocoding from Open Dev MM

Mines¶

EITI

  • PDFs and Excel data for MEITI Reports

Oil and Gas¶

EITI

  • PDFs and Excel data for MEITI Reports

Power¶

Ministry of Electricity and Energy State/Region profiles

  • data on power plants spread across multiple HTML pages

Viz 3 - Regional development indicators¶

Show disparaties in regional development through these indicators

  • Electrification
  • Employment
  • Poverty, deprivation

These indicators are chosen because they are the most directly linkable to investment projects. We want to counter the govt's line that investment brings development.

Data Sources¶

Electrification¶

Ministry of Electricity and Energy State/Region profiles

  • data on power plants spread across multiple HTML pages

Employment¶

2014 Census data on labor

  • PDF of thematic report on labor force - contains aggregated tables
  • REDATUM Online tool to extract census data

Poverty, Deprivation¶

World Bank - Multidimensional Welfare in Myanmar Report

  • PDF Report

The WB report does not provide the raw data - but it is all derived from census data. We can look at the criteria that they consider constitutes deprivation to recalculate using census data

Viz 4 - Conflict and land seizures¶

Show that locations of conflicts and armed groups are usually in areas where investment projects are located

  • Locations of conflict
  • Locations of armed groups

Show that we are at the precipice of an even more precarious situation for land seisures with the new VFV law

  • VFV and potential for land seizures (contestation of land)

Data Sources¶

Locations of conflict¶

Data from ACLED and TAF

  • Google Drive folder of Eva's analysis
  • Original ACLED Source

MIPS Annual Peace and Security Review

  • PDF Report

Locations of armed groups¶

Asia Foundation's Contested Areas of Myanmar Report

  • PDF Report - map on pg 27 - note: this does not include militias or border guard forces

VFV and potential for land seizures (contestation of land)¶

Mekong Regional Land Governance - Large-Scale Land Acquisitions for Agricultural Development in Myanmar: A Review of Past and Current Processes Report

  • PDF Report contains state/region level data - table 4 on pg 40

GAD's Township profiles has township level land use data

  • PDFs of township profiles collected by MIMU
